00:33:10.370 --> 00:33:12.953 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: You've certainly gained
an enormous amount of insights

00:33:12.953 --> 00:33:14.920 align:middle line:84%
and I want you to share
some of-- you know,

00:33:14.920 --> 00:33:17.750 align:middle line:84%
if you could kind of
encapsulate some of your tips.

00:33:17.750 --> 00:33:20.980 align:middle line:84%
And we have a sheet
here of your tips.

00:33:20.980 --> 00:33:22.910 align:middle line:84%
These are spiritual
tips, but I just

00:33:22.910 --> 00:33:24.990 align:middle line:84%
want to ask you before
we go through those,

00:33:24.990 --> 00:33:27.650 align:middle line:90%
can you hear Lorrin now, today?

00:33:27.650 --> 00:33:31.530 align:middle line:84%
Can you hear her throughout
your daily walking life?

00:33:31.530 --> 00:33:34.020 align:middle line:90%
>>KAIN: I feel her all the time.

00:33:34.020 --> 00:33:38.270 align:middle line:84%
I hear her also, but I kind of
feel-- she told me one time,

00:33:38.270 --> 00:33:40.330 align:middle line:84%
she said, if I told
you everything,

00:33:40.330 --> 00:33:42.010 align:middle line:90%
it would take the surprise away.

00:33:42.010 --> 00:33:45.604 align:middle line:84%
So I try to just
ask for her energy.

00:33:45.604 --> 00:33:47.020 align:middle line:84%
Of course, sometimes
I'll be like,

00:33:47.020 --> 00:33:48.478 align:middle line:84%
you know, I need
help here, Lorrin,

00:33:48.478 --> 00:33:50.640 align:middle line:84%
or-- I know she's
in an amazing place.

00:33:50.640 --> 00:33:52.182 align:middle line:84%
I've never worried
about her ever.

00:33:52.182 --> 00:33:53.890 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: Has she
communicated that to you?

00:33:53.890 --> 00:33:54.920 align:middle line:90%
>>KAIN: Yes, yes.

00:33:54.920 --> 00:33:55.901 align:middle line:90%
I mean, I knew before.

00:33:55.901 --> 00:33:56.400 align:middle line:90%
She said--

00:33:56.400 --> 00:33:57.390 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Where is she?

00:33:57.390 --> 00:33:58.960 align:middle line:84%
>>KAIN: I think
she's everywhere.

00:33:58.960 --> 00:34:00.136 align:middle line:90%
I think she's everywhere.

00:34:00.136 --> 00:34:02.260 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: But when you say
she's in an amazing place,

00:34:02.260 --> 00:34:03.250 align:middle line:90%
does she describe it?

00:34:03.250 --> 00:34:05.130 align:middle line:84%
>>KAIN: She said
one time, clearly,

00:34:05.130 --> 00:34:08.845 align:middle line:84%
she said, if you could
see what I see, mom.

00:34:08.845 --> 00:34:10.719 align:middle line:84%
I think she was like--
and when she was here,

00:34:10.719 --> 00:34:12.270 align:middle line:84%
I think she was in
a physical body,

00:34:12.270 --> 00:34:13.820 align:middle line:84%
but I think she also
had the capacity

00:34:13.820 --> 00:34:15.090 align:middle line:90%
to be in that spirit realm.

00:34:15.090 --> 00:34:16.230 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: To travel, mm-hm.

00:34:16.230 --> 00:34:20.310 align:middle line:84%
>>KAIN: Just to be completely
away from her body.

00:34:20.310 --> 00:34:23.060 align:middle line:84%
And I knew that about her,
so it would make me mad

00:34:23.060 --> 00:34:25.719 align:middle line:84%
that she had the capacity to
pull herself out of her body

00:34:25.719 --> 00:34:27.370 align:middle line:84%
and then I would be
here caring for it.

00:34:27.370 --> 00:34:28.850 align:middle line:84%
It's like, get
back in your body.

00:34:28.850 --> 00:34:31.332 align:middle line:84%
I'm like, I know you're
out gallivanting,

00:34:31.332 --> 00:34:32.790 align:middle line:84%
but I've got to
clean up this mess.

00:34:32.790 --> 00:34:36.560 align:middle line:84%
Sometimes things were a little
messy her last year of life.

00:34:36.560 --> 00:34:39.010 align:middle line:84%
But I think one of the
most profound things she

00:34:39.010 --> 00:34:41.570 align:middle line:84%
said to me recently when I was
at the AutismOne Conference,

00:34:41.570 --> 00:34:44.360 align:middle line:84%
because that is-- my
heart is with children

00:34:44.360 --> 00:34:45.400 align:middle line:90%
who are vaccine injured.

00:34:45.400 --> 00:34:47.650 align:middle line:84%
All children-- all
children who are unique

00:34:47.650 --> 00:34:50.679 align:middle line:84%
are here just to do exactly
what they're here to do.

00:34:50.679 --> 00:34:54.070 align:middle line:84%
But, of course, I'm
very sensitive speaking

00:34:54.070 --> 00:34:56.260 align:middle line:84%
to children who are
vaccine injured.

00:34:56.260 --> 00:34:59.540 align:middle line:84%
And so I'm always asking
her, and usually she says,

00:34:59.540 --> 00:35:01.010 align:middle line:90%
make it fun, mom.

00:35:01.010 --> 00:35:04.290 align:middle line:84%
And that day, she said, mom,
tell them it was worth it.

00:35:04.290 --> 00:35:06.370 align:middle line:84%
And it just came
so clear to me--

00:35:06.370 --> 00:35:06.870 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Wow.

00:35:06.870 --> 00:35:09.810 align:middle line:84%
>>KAIN: -and so strong and
it just-- that's Lorrin.

00:35:09.810 --> 00:35:12.010 align:middle line:84%
She just is always
full of love and I

00:35:12.010 --> 00:35:14.250 align:middle line:84%
want to really
remind parents first

00:35:14.250 --> 00:35:16.020 align:middle line:90%
to take care of themselves.

00:35:16.020 --> 00:35:18.240 align:middle line:84%
We can't do anything--
we can't be spiritual,

00:35:18.240 --> 00:35:21.120 align:middle line:84%
we can't be good parents, we
can't be good to ourselves

00:35:21.120 --> 00:35:23.490 align:middle line:84%
if we're exhausted and not
taking care of ourselves

00:35:23.490 --> 00:35:25.520 align:middle line:90%
and everything falls apart.

00:35:25.520 --> 00:35:27.807 align:middle line:84%
And I think that's typically
what mothers don't do.

00:35:27.807 --> 00:35:28.390 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Right.

00:35:28.390 --> 00:35:30.410 align:middle line:84%
>>KAIN: First, they
do everything else.

00:35:30.410 --> 00:35:32.640 align:middle line:84%
And because they think
that's-- and I did the same.

00:35:32.640 --> 00:35:33.685 align:middle line:90%
You know, I was a martyr.

00:35:33.685 --> 00:35:34.865 align:middle line:90%
I was beating myself up.

00:35:34.865 --> 00:35:37.250 align:middle line:84%
I was exhausted and I
couldn't hold it together.

00:35:37.250 --> 00:35:38.950 align:middle line:84%
I couldn't make life
and death decisions

00:35:38.950 --> 00:35:41.054 align:middle line:84%
because I just-- I
was barely breathing.

00:35:41.054 --> 00:35:42.720 align:middle line:84%
So I want to remind
parents and families

00:35:42.720 --> 00:35:45.040 align:middle line:84%
to take care of
themselves first.

00:35:45.040 --> 00:35:46.346 align:middle line:90%
And make it fun.

00:35:46.346 --> 00:35:47.970 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: You made an
interesting comment

00:35:47.970 --> 00:35:52.280 align:middle line:84%
before the show about 95%
of parents with children

00:35:52.280 --> 00:35:55.610 align:middle line:84%
with disabilities
don't stay together.

00:35:55.610 --> 00:35:56.820 align:middle line:90%
That's a very high number.

00:35:56.820 --> 00:36:01.120 align:middle line:84%
What could you contribute
to allow that statistic

00:36:01.120 --> 00:36:02.774 align:middle line:90%
to go down?

00:36:02.774 --> 00:36:04.190 align:middle line:84%
>>KAIN: I think a
big part-- well,

00:36:04.190 --> 00:36:06.510 align:middle line:84%
I mean, grief-- everyone
grieves differently.

00:36:06.510 --> 00:36:07.080 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Yes

00:36:07.080 --> 00:36:12.130 align:middle line:84%
>>KAIN: And kids, you
know, siblings and couples,

00:36:12.130 --> 00:36:13.180 align:middle line:90%
we grieve differently.

00:36:13.180 --> 00:36:14.890 align:middle line:84%
And that's a very
difficult thing,

00:36:14.890 --> 00:36:16.851 align:middle line:84%
because typically we're
always somewhere else.

00:36:16.851 --> 00:36:18.350 align:middle line:84%
It doesn't matter
how smart you are,

00:36:18.350 --> 00:36:21.149 align:middle line:84%
it doesn't matter how educated
you are, or spiritual.

00:36:21.149 --> 00:36:21.690 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Yeah.

00:36:21.690 --> 00:36:23.820 align:middle line:84%
>>KAIN: Everybody
does that differently.

00:36:23.820 --> 00:36:26.140 align:middle line:84%
I think communicating
and reminding

00:36:26.140 --> 00:36:28.330 align:middle line:84%
that the couple,
the family together,

00:36:28.330 --> 00:36:29.460 align:middle line:90%
has to be taken care of.

00:36:29.460 --> 00:36:32.640 align:middle line:84%
And a lot of times, especially
I did, everything was Lorrin.

00:36:32.640 --> 00:36:33.807 align:middle line:90%
Everything I did was Lorrin.

00:36:33.807 --> 00:36:34.390 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Right.

00:36:34.390 --> 00:36:35.760 align:middle line:90%
>>KAIN: And the coping skills?

00:36:35.760 --> 00:36:37.540 align:middle line:84%
I didn't get married
and think that we

00:36:37.540 --> 00:36:40.240 align:middle line:84%
would be deciding if
we're going to pull

00:36:40.240 --> 00:36:41.240 align:middle line:90%
the plug on my daughter.

00:36:41.240 --> 00:36:41.580 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Right.

00:36:41.580 --> 00:36:43.038 align:middle line:84%
>>KAIN: That is
not anything I ever

00:36:43.038 --> 00:36:44.730 align:middle line:84%
thought I would be
making a decision on.

00:36:44.730 --> 00:36:46.350 align:middle line:90%
So-- and it's stressful.

00:36:46.350 --> 00:36:49.330 align:middle line:84%
I lived in the hospital
for two years with her.

00:36:49.330 --> 00:36:50.820 align:middle line:90%
It's high stress.

00:36:50.820 --> 00:36:52.659 align:middle line:90%
And not having rules.

00:36:52.659 --> 00:36:54.200 align:middle line:84%
And back then, there
was no internet.

00:36:54.200 --> 00:36:56.030 align:middle line:84%
I couldn't get on
the internet and say,

00:36:56.030 --> 00:36:57.340 align:middle line:90%
does anybody feel like me?

00:36:57.340 --> 00:36:59.406 align:middle line:84%
Now, at least there's
tons of families,

00:36:59.406 --> 00:37:00.780 align:middle line:84%
there's tons of
parents out there

00:37:00.780 --> 00:37:02.107 align:middle line:90%
connecting and supporting.

00:37:02.107 --> 00:37:02.940 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: That's good.

00:37:02.940 --> 00:37:04.260 align:middle line:84%
And they're doing it
together because there's

00:37:04.260 --> 00:37:06.160 align:middle line:84%
a lot more awareness
around it now.

00:37:06.160 --> 00:37:11.410 align:middle line:84%
But in the past, maybe the other
parent felt alone completely

00:37:11.410 --> 00:37:12.480 align:middle line:90%
>>KAIN: Yeah.

00:37:12.480 --> 00:37:15.280 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: It's something that--
do you talk about this as well

00:37:15.280 --> 00:37:17.329 align:middle line:84%
in the conferences when
you go to talk to--

00:37:17.329 --> 00:37:18.120 align:middle line:90%
>>KAIN: Absolutely.

00:37:18.120 --> 00:37:19.240 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: -the AutismOne
and so forth?

00:37:19.240 --> 00:37:20.031 align:middle line:90%
>>KAIN: Absolutely.

00:37:20.031 --> 00:37:22.490 align:middle line:84%
I think first and foremost,
we take care of ourselves.

00:37:22.490 --> 00:37:23.890 align:middle line:84%
And I think then
it kind of opens

00:37:23.890 --> 00:37:25.570 align:middle line:90%
the gateway for the intuition.

00:37:25.570 --> 00:37:27.080 align:middle line:84%
And I always try
to remind parents

00:37:27.080 --> 00:37:30.340 align:middle line:84%
that our children are here doing
exactly what they need to do.

00:37:30.340 --> 00:37:32.040 align:middle line:84%
And parenting children
who are unique

00:37:32.040 --> 00:37:34.730 align:middle line:84%
is the most important job
that you'll ever have.

00:37:34.730 --> 00:37:38.490 align:middle line:84%
The Native American community
totally holds these kids up.

00:37:38.490 --> 00:37:41.410 align:middle line:84%
They know how important and
how magical these children are

00:37:41.410 --> 00:37:44.100 align:middle line:84%
and how wise that they
came here to teach us.

00:37:44.100 --> 00:37:45.600 align:middle line:84%
Because with
Lorrin, I think, she

00:37:45.600 --> 00:37:48.059 align:middle line:84%
came here to do a
really tough job.

00:37:48.059 --> 00:37:49.475 align:middle line:84%
You know, people
would look at her

00:37:49.475 --> 00:37:51.308 align:middle line:84%
and say, why would you
ever want to do that?

00:37:51.308 --> 00:37:53.510 align:middle line:84%
But look what she has
done and the power

00:37:53.510 --> 00:37:56.280 align:middle line:84%
of her and her belief
in God and her faith

00:37:56.280 --> 00:38:00.840 align:middle line:84%
to trust me as her mother and to
go out and be in the community.

00:38:00.840 --> 00:38:03.640 align:middle line:84%
And so I'm doing my half of
my soul agreement, I hope.

00:38:03.640 --> 00:38:06.096 align:middle line:84%
I'm sure there's more,
but that's my commitment

00:38:06.096 --> 00:38:07.720 align:middle line:84%
to Lorrin because I
think she came here

00:38:07.720 --> 00:38:09.590 align:middle line:84%
to do exactly what
she needed to do.

00:38:09.590 --> 00:38:11.322 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Which is to communicate?

00:38:11.322 --> 00:38:12.280 align:middle line:90%
>>KAIN: To communicate.

00:38:12.280 --> 00:38:15.280 align:middle line:84%
To change, hopefully, the
vaccine program, the way we

00:38:15.280 --> 00:38:16.120 align:middle line:90%
treat families.

00:38:16.120 --> 00:38:20.830 align:middle line:84%
To remind parents that children
who are unique are valuable.

00:38:20.830 --> 00:38:23.640 align:middle line:84%
Every soul is important,
no matter their ability.

00:38:23.640 --> 00:38:25.850 align:middle line:84%
To remember that we
can look into the eyes

00:38:25.850 --> 00:38:27.249 align:middle line:90%
and see the soul of somebody.

00:38:27.249 --> 00:38:28.540 align:middle line:90%
They don't have to communicate.

00:38:28.540 --> 00:38:29.620 align:middle line:90%
They don't have to walk.

00:38:29.620 --> 00:38:34.060 align:middle line:84%
And to not discount any of us
because some are able-bodied

00:38:34.060 --> 00:38:34.970 align:middle line:90%
and some aren't.

00:38:34.970 --> 00:38:35.740 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Yes.

00:38:35.740 --> 00:38:38.050 align:middle line:90%
>>KAIN: Everybody's important.

00:38:38.050 --> 00:38:40.360 align:middle line:84%
And I think creating
our own reality,

00:38:40.360 --> 00:38:43.430 align:middle line:84%
I mean, I really had to
change my perspective when

00:38:43.430 --> 00:38:45.350 align:middle line:84%
I was suffering and
I felt there was

00:38:45.350 --> 00:38:47.820 align:middle line:84%
lack in Lorrin, that's
what I would get.

00:38:47.820 --> 00:38:49.525 align:middle line:84%
And when I accepted
her and saw that she

00:38:49.525 --> 00:38:52.390 align:middle line:84%
was perfect the way she was,
then I would see the magic.

00:38:52.390 --> 00:38:57.690 align:middle line:84%
And the more magic I felt,
because she always was magical,

00:38:57.690 --> 00:38:59.770 align:middle line:84%
then the more magic we
brought into our life.

00:38:59.770 --> 00:39:01.936 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: That was one of the
tips that you have here,

00:39:01.936 --> 00:39:04.690 align:middle line:84%
is that the world
that we live in

00:39:04.690 --> 00:39:06.979 align:middle line:84%
is a projection of
our own thoughts.

00:39:06.979 --> 00:39:07.770 align:middle line:90%
>>KAIN: Absolutely.

00:39:07.770 --> 00:39:10.420 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: So if you
felt lack, then

00:39:10.420 --> 00:39:13.670 align:middle line:84%
you would accept-- that's what
you would attract is lack.

00:39:13.670 --> 00:39:17.059 align:middle line:84%
And she taught you this
in some way, right?

00:39:17.059 --> 00:39:17.850 align:middle line:90%
>>KAIN: Absolutely.

00:39:17.850 --> 00:39:19.920 align:middle line:84%
And my friend told me,
he says, if you ever

00:39:19.920 --> 00:39:21.336 align:middle line:84%
wonder what you
believe, just look

00:39:21.336 --> 00:39:23.040 align:middle line:84%
what you've surrounded
yourself with.

00:39:23.040 --> 00:39:23.623 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Right.

00:39:23.623 --> 00:39:26.400 align:middle line:84%
>>KAIN: And I believe
that there's magic

00:39:26.400 --> 00:39:28.280 align:middle line:84%
and I believe that I
can do anything I want.

00:39:28.280 --> 00:39:31.190 align:middle line:84%
I mean, look, I'm here with
you talking about the story.

00:39:31.190 --> 00:39:32.080 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Yes.

00:39:32.080 --> 00:39:35.020 align:middle line:84%
>>KAIN: I just felt-- and I
felt very much as her parent,

00:39:35.020 --> 00:39:36.200 align:middle line:90%
but I was in school.

00:39:36.200 --> 00:39:38.920 align:middle line:84%
I mean, I feel like-- you
know, Lorrin always said,

00:39:38.920 --> 00:39:40.560 align:middle line:90%
like is but a coffee break, mom.

00:39:40.560 --> 00:39:41.544 align:middle line:90%
Get over yourself.

00:39:41.544 --> 00:39:42.460 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: She said that?

00:39:42.460 --> 00:39:44.780 align:middle line:84%
>>KAIN: Oh, she was just
very whatever with me

00:39:44.780 --> 00:39:46.110 align:middle line:90%
because I was always drama.

00:39:46.110 --> 00:39:49.000 align:middle line:84%
She's just, you know,
get over it, mom.

00:39:49.000 --> 00:39:53.480 align:middle line:84%
Because she just had this
amazing belief and confidence

00:39:53.480 --> 00:39:55.727 align:middle line:84%
and trust and she
always exuded that.

00:39:55.727 --> 00:39:57.810 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: That everything
was going to be all right?

00:39:57.810 --> 00:39:58.492 align:middle line:90%
>>KAIN: Mm-hm.

00:39:58.492 --> 00:40:00.700 align:middle line:84%
And ironically, she still
loved fashion and chocolate

00:40:00.700 --> 00:40:01.980 align:middle line:90%
and wanted to shop.

00:40:01.980 --> 00:40:06.590 align:middle line:84%
But she always-- she was so
loving, at her funeral someone

00:40:06.590 --> 00:40:09.770 align:middle line:84%
said it so perfectly that
Lorrin made people feel safe.

00:40:09.770 --> 00:40:12.390 align:middle line:84%
And that's so strange
because you really

00:40:12.390 --> 00:40:13.970 align:middle line:90%
had to experience it.

00:40:13.970 --> 00:40:15.770 align:middle line:84%
And I knew when she
was crossing over,

00:40:15.770 --> 00:40:18.170 align:middle line:84%
that would be what I
missed the most in my home.

00:40:18.170 --> 00:40:20.390 align:middle line:84%
I know she's still there
and all that, but just

00:40:20.390 --> 00:40:24.290 align:middle line:84%
walking into a house that is
filled with love and trust.

00:40:24.290 --> 00:40:27.340 align:middle line:84%
And so I just held
her up and just

00:40:27.340 --> 00:40:29.550 align:middle line:84%
really wanted to learn
everything I could from her.

00:40:29.550 --> 00:40:33.180 align:middle line:84%
Because I felt if you've
come here to be in this body

00:40:33.180 --> 00:40:34.720 align:middle line:84%
and you're putting
up with all this,

00:40:34.720 --> 00:40:36.120 align:middle line:84%
I need to really
learn my lessons

00:40:36.120 --> 00:40:37.769 align:middle line:90%
that you're here to teach--

00:40:37.769 --> 00:40:38.310 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: And--

00:40:38.310 --> 00:40:39.435 align:middle line:90%
>>KAIN: -as quick as I can.

00:40:39.435 --> 00:40:41.250 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: And is
that-- those lessons

00:40:41.250 --> 00:40:44.240 align:middle line:84%
that she taught you
are continuing to come,

00:40:44.240 --> 00:40:44.790 align:middle line:90%
aren't they?

00:40:44.790 --> 00:40:45.080 align:middle line:90%
>>KAIN: Absolutely.

00:40:45.080 --> 00:40:47.100 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: I mean, it's
not just these tips

00:40:47.100 --> 00:40:49.720 align:middle line:84%
that you wrote here
and the spiritual tips.

00:40:49.720 --> 00:40:52.309 align:middle line:84%
You have a lot more that
you've learned, haven't you?

00:40:52.309 --> 00:40:53.600 align:middle line:90%
>>KAIN: I'm learning every day.

00:40:53.600 --> 00:40:53.980 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Yeah.

00:40:53.980 --> 00:40:55.729 align:middle line:84%
>>KAIN: -and I challenge
myself every day.

00:40:55.729 --> 00:40:59.030 align:middle line:84%
And I don't-- you know, Lorrin
certainly wants me to tell

00:40:59.030 --> 00:41:01.024 align:middle line:84%
everybody that I was
not a sainted parent,

00:41:01.024 --> 00:41:01.940 align:middle line:90%
not a perfect parent--

00:41:01.940 --> 00:41:02.440 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: None of us are.

00:41:02.440 --> 00:41:03.689 align:middle line:90%
>>KAIN: -not a perfect mother.

00:41:03.689 --> 00:41:04.890 align:middle line:90%
I did a lot of things wrong.

00:41:04.890 --> 00:41:07.630 align:middle line:84%
I went in kicking and
screaming and crying.

00:41:07.630 --> 00:41:10.090 align:middle line:84%
So it wasn't that I
was just zen with her

00:41:10.090 --> 00:41:12.610 align:middle line:84%
and oh, great, this
is going to be lovely.

00:41:12.610 --> 00:41:14.750 align:middle line:84%
I had to learn by
letting everything

00:41:14.750 --> 00:41:16.600 align:middle line:84%
go that I thought was
important in my life.

00:41:16.600 --> 00:41:17.880 align:middle line:90%
I lost everything.

00:41:17.880 --> 00:41:19.530 align:middle line:84%
And I never thought
that I could live

00:41:19.530 --> 00:41:22.306 align:middle line:84%
and be happy without
having another child.

00:41:22.306 --> 00:41:23.930 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: Did you ever
decide to do that?

00:41:23.930 --> 00:41:24.846 align:middle line:90%
To have another child?

00:41:24.846 --> 00:41:26.170 align:middle line:90%
>>KAIN: It just didn't work.

00:41:26.170 --> 00:41:27.550 align:middle line:90%
I wanted to desperately.

00:41:27.550 --> 00:41:30.780 align:middle line:84%
And I really believed there
was a time that I couldn't even

00:41:30.780 --> 00:41:32.400 align:middle line:84%
think that thought
without crying.

00:41:32.400 --> 00:41:34.950 align:middle line:84%
I just thought, she's going
to die, I'm going to be alone,

00:41:34.950 --> 00:41:36.220 align:middle line:90%
and I'm not going to be a mom.

00:41:36.220 --> 00:41:37.710 align:middle line:90%
I miss being a mom.

00:41:37.710 --> 00:41:39.530 align:middle line:90%
I miss all of that.

00:41:39.530 --> 00:41:42.600 align:middle line:84%
You know, of course I
miss so many things.

00:41:42.600 --> 00:41:46.370 align:middle line:84%
But I realize I'm here to
do exactly what I'm doing.

00:41:46.370 --> 00:41:49.130 align:middle line:84%
And if I can help
one family and help

00:41:49.130 --> 00:41:52.960 align:middle line:84%
one parent to shift their
perspective from fear and lack

00:41:52.960 --> 00:41:57.010 align:middle line:84%
to love and acceptance and
embracing and supporting

00:41:57.010 --> 00:41:58.460 align:middle line:90%
and enjoying--

00:41:58.460 --> 00:42:00.600 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: Well, you're
a mother to many.

00:42:00.600 --> 00:42:02.640 align:middle line:84%
I mean, consider
what you do now.

00:42:02.640 --> 00:42:07.250 align:middle line:84%
You are a support to mothers and
you're a support to children.

00:42:07.250 --> 00:42:08.790 align:middle line:84%
So essentially,
you're the mother

00:42:08.790 --> 00:42:13.400 align:middle line:84%
of many, many children,
not just one anymore.

00:42:13.400 --> 00:42:14.150 align:middle line:90%
>>KAIN: I love it.

00:42:14.150 --> 00:42:16.120 align:middle line:84%
And I get to meet all
kinds of awesome kids.

00:42:16.120 --> 00:42:18.100 align:middle line:90%
And they are so magical.

00:42:18.100 --> 00:42:19.470 align:middle line:90%
Our kids are so magical.

00:42:19.470 --> 00:42:23.100 align:middle line:84%
We have to know
that's true and we

00:42:23.100 --> 00:42:25.909 align:middle line:84%
shouldn't be surprised
by the magic of Lorrin

00:42:25.909 --> 00:42:26.950 align:middle line:90%
and all these other kids.

00:42:26.950 --> 00:42:28.324 align:middle line:84%
We should expect
it and we should

00:42:28.324 --> 00:42:31.460 align:middle line:84%
be listening harder and
being open with our hearts.

00:42:31.460 --> 00:42:34.270 align:middle line:84%
Not with our minds and not
with what people tell us to be.

00:42:34.270 --> 00:42:36.410 align:middle line:84%
But to be listening
with our hearts

00:42:36.410 --> 00:42:37.910 align:middle line:90%
and hearing these children.

00:42:37.910 --> 00:42:39.819 align:middle line:84%
Because, I mean, I look
at them all the time

00:42:39.819 --> 00:42:42.360 align:middle line:84%
and I see their eyes and I see
into their soul and it's like,

00:42:42.360 --> 00:42:44.630 align:middle line:84%
I don't understand
everything they're saying.

00:42:44.630 --> 00:42:46.600 align:middle line:84%
But I know they're
communicating.

00:42:46.600 --> 00:42:48.860 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: So tell me a little
bit more, if you can,

00:42:48.860 --> 00:42:53.870 align:middle line:84%
I'm very curious about the
world that Lorrin is in.

00:42:53.870 --> 00:42:58.130 align:middle line:84%
If you could give us any
sense of pictures of what

00:42:58.130 --> 00:42:59.270 align:middle line:90%
she describes.

00:42:59.270 --> 00:43:03.160 align:middle line:84%
And you said that if you
could see where she is now,

00:43:03.160 --> 00:43:05.060 align:middle line:84%
you would understand
that she's fine.

00:43:05.060 --> 00:43:07.300 align:middle line:84%
Has she ever given you
descriptions of that

00:43:07.300 --> 00:43:12.010 align:middle line:84%
or feelings or anything that
you could communicate to us?

00:43:12.010 --> 00:43:14.720 align:middle line:84%
>>KAIN: It-- a long time
ago when I would meditate,

00:43:14.720 --> 00:43:17.180 align:middle line:84%
I started seeing this
bright, bright light.

00:43:17.180 --> 00:43:20.430 align:middle line:84%
And I understood that
she was showing me

00:43:20.430 --> 00:43:22.470 align:middle line:84%
her light, which
was also my light.

00:43:22.470 --> 00:43:23.580 align:middle line:84%
She would just-- you
know, I would see this.

00:43:23.580 --> 00:43:24.955 align:middle line:84%
I would meditate
and I would just

00:43:24.955 --> 00:43:28.440 align:middle line:84%
feel this enormous presence and
love and energy and perfection

00:43:28.440 --> 00:43:29.720 align:middle line:90%
and just power.

00:43:29.720 --> 00:43:31.600 align:middle line:84%
And then she would
say, mom, this is you.

00:43:31.600 --> 00:43:33.970 align:middle line:84%
You see it in me because
this is who you are.

00:43:33.970 --> 00:43:35.520 align:middle line:90%
We are one.

00:43:35.520 --> 00:43:37.840 align:middle line:84%
And I have had
times where I just

00:43:37.840 --> 00:43:41.412 align:middle line:84%
feel this unbelievably powerful
feeling of love, of course.

00:43:41.412 --> 00:43:42.995 align:middle line:84%
And then it would
go, and it's like, I

00:43:42.995 --> 00:43:45.350 align:middle line:90%
want that back, you know.

00:43:45.350 --> 00:43:47.450 align:middle line:84%
I have to be physical
here right now.

00:43:47.450 --> 00:43:48.560 align:middle line:90%
I'm still physical.

00:43:48.560 --> 00:43:53.870 align:middle line:84%
When she comes in-- after she
died-- at first I just saw her.

00:43:53.870 --> 00:43:55.330 align:middle line:84%
And sometimes I
see her in my car

00:43:55.330 --> 00:43:56.210 align:middle line:90%
and I yell at her in the car.

00:43:56.210 --> 00:43:58.126 align:middle line:84%
That's where I, like,
yell at her all the time

00:43:58.126 --> 00:44:00.710 align:middle line:84%
and just have that-- I yelled
at her when she was here, too.

00:44:00.710 --> 00:44:02.600 align:middle line:90%
It's like, just whatever it is.

00:44:02.600 --> 00:44:04.290 align:middle line:84%
Like mothers, just
like where are you?

00:44:04.290 --> 00:44:04.950 align:middle line:90%
Or what are you doing?

00:44:04.950 --> 00:44:05.840 align:middle line:90%
Or what's this about?

00:44:05.840 --> 00:44:09.130 align:middle line:84%
Just like, I need a sign,
a big sign, you know.

00:44:09.130 --> 00:44:11.380 align:middle line:84%
Because I just always yelled
at her when she was here.

00:44:11.380 --> 00:44:12.713 align:middle line:90%
It was like, what are you doing?

00:44:12.713 --> 00:44:15.500 align:middle line:84%
We'd argue and she'd just look
or laugh or just roll her eyes

00:44:15.500 --> 00:44:19.114 align:middle line:84%
at me, because I'm
very verbal, obviously.

00:44:19.114 --> 00:44:22.570 align:middle line:84%
But she puts the fire
alarms off a lot,

00:44:22.570 --> 00:44:25.120 align:middle line:84%
and I asked her one time
before she died, I would just,

00:44:25.120 --> 00:44:28.210 align:middle line:84%
you know, how will I
know where you are?

00:44:28.210 --> 00:44:32.750 align:middle line:84%
And she said, when you see love
and magic and light in nature,

00:44:32.750 --> 00:44:34.790 align:middle line:84%
in anything
beautiful, I am there.

00:44:34.790 --> 00:44:39.670 align:middle line:84%
And that's sweet and not very
specific, but I have to trust.

00:44:39.670 --> 00:44:42.530 align:middle line:90%
I have to-- I trust in her.

00:44:42.530 --> 00:44:45.740 align:middle line:84%
And so how do I--
where is she at now?

00:44:45.740 --> 00:44:48.750 align:middle line:84%
She comes to me now and she
comes to me as a perfect

00:44:48.750 --> 00:44:52.542 align:middle line:84%
person, a perfect body,
which really throws me off

00:44:52.542 --> 00:44:54.250 align:middle line:84%
and it's really hard
for me because I'm--

00:44:54.250 --> 00:44:55.280 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Standing and--

00:44:55.280 --> 00:44:56.113 align:middle line:90%
>>KAIN: Just-- yeah.

00:44:56.113 --> 00:44:58.870 align:middle line:84%
A lot of-- she comes to
people all the time dancing

00:44:58.870 --> 00:45:01.859 align:middle line:84%
or ice skating, a
beautiful ballerina.

00:45:01.859 --> 00:45:03.900 align:middle line:84%
And then sometimes she
comes to different people,

00:45:03.900 --> 00:45:05.050 align:middle line:84%
I'm just saying to
a lot of different--

00:45:05.050 --> 00:45:06.690 align:middle line:84%
she'll come in eating all
kinds of different foods.

00:45:06.690 --> 00:45:09.065 align:middle line:84%
Like olives and chocolate and
this and just popping food.

00:45:09.065 --> 00:45:12.730 align:middle line:84%
And I see her running around
all the time, just really busy.

00:45:12.730 --> 00:45:15.350 align:middle line:84%
But when I'm meditating, she
comes in-- she'll come to me

00:45:15.350 --> 00:45:17.940 align:middle line:84%
and she'll hold my hand and
she'll look into my eyes.

00:45:17.940 --> 00:45:20.074 align:middle line:84%
And she has a crooked eye,
and she just does this.

00:45:20.074 --> 00:45:21.740 align:middle line:84%
So that's when I know
it's like serious.

00:45:21.740 --> 00:45:23.146 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Ah.

00:45:23.146 --> 00:45:25.020 align:middle line:84%
>>KAIN: Every night I
feel like when I sleep,

00:45:25.020 --> 00:45:27.450 align:middle line:84%
I was like-- because we
slept together all the time,

00:45:27.450 --> 00:45:29.000 align:middle line:90%
so I feel her energy.

00:45:29.000 --> 00:45:31.420 align:middle line:84%
A lot of times, it's more
of a feeling than a vision.

00:45:31.420 --> 00:45:34.500 align:middle line:84%
But when I do see see her
and she comes in perfect,

00:45:34.500 --> 00:45:36.169 align:middle line:90%
it throws me out of meditation.

00:45:36.169 --> 00:45:38.460 align:middle line:84%
And I just say, I love that
you have this perfect body,

00:45:38.460 --> 00:45:41.570 align:middle line:84%
but it's hard for me
because like part of you

00:45:41.570 --> 00:45:44.359 align:middle line:84%
was the crooked feet and the
eye crooked and the arms.

00:45:44.359 --> 00:45:45.650 align:middle line:90%
But she still comes in with it.

00:45:45.650 --> 00:45:47.774 align:middle line:84%
You know, she's going to
do what she's going to do.

00:45:47.774 --> 00:45:48.610 align:middle line:90%
[LISA LAUGHING]

00:45:48.610 --> 00:45:51.390 align:middle line:84%
And I asked her one time when
I was meditating, I said,

00:45:51.390 --> 00:45:53.090 align:middle line:90%
what do you miss most?

00:45:53.090 --> 00:45:55.289 align:middle line:84%
And she said, the
physical touch.

00:45:55.289 --> 00:45:55.830 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Yeah.

00:45:55.830 --> 00:45:58.190 align:middle line:84%
>>KAIN: And so that
just reminds me,

00:45:58.190 --> 00:46:01.020 align:middle line:84%
we-- I just feel like this
is just such a small time.

00:46:01.020 --> 00:46:03.970 align:middle line:84%
I don't feel-- I feel like we
have many lives, or you know,

00:46:03.970 --> 00:46:05.690 align:middle line:84%
she said really
they're parallel lives,

00:46:05.690 --> 00:46:08.331 align:middle line:84%
but I know that's probably more
confusing to really talk about.

00:46:08.331 --> 00:46:09.580 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: No, it's actually not.

00:46:09.580 --> 00:46:13.530 align:middle line:84%
That is a question that I have
about these parallel universes

00:46:13.530 --> 00:46:17.880 align:middle line:84%
and that we do walk
in the same time,

00:46:17.880 --> 00:46:21.030 align:middle line:84%
although there is no time,
in just different realms.

00:46:21.030 --> 00:46:22.990 align:middle line:84%
Is that basically what
she's communicating?

00:46:22.990 --> 00:46:24.000 align:middle line:90%
Is that what you feel?

00:46:24.000 --> 00:46:27.010 align:middle line:84%
>>KAIN: That's-- I don't
fully understand it.

00:46:27.010 --> 00:46:27.900 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Not yet.

00:46:27.900 --> 00:46:29.870 align:middle line:84%
>>KAIN: You know, it's
always like the onion.

00:46:29.870 --> 00:46:32.407 align:middle line:84%
You know, I get to these
places of like oh, I get that.

00:46:32.407 --> 00:46:32.990 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Right.

00:46:32.990 --> 00:46:33.270 align:middle line:90%
Of course.

00:46:33.270 --> 00:46:34.780 align:middle line:84%
>>KAIN: People talk about
it, people talk about it,

00:46:34.780 --> 00:46:35.400 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: As you're ready, yeah.

00:46:35.400 --> 00:46:37.550 align:middle line:84%
>>KAIN: I believe it's
a parallel universe.

00:46:37.550 --> 00:46:38.510 align:middle line:90%
There is no time.

00:46:38.510 --> 00:46:40.709 align:middle line:90%
So how silly of me to worry.

00:46:40.709 --> 00:46:41.250 align:middle line:90%
Of all of us.

00:46:41.250 --> 00:46:44.170 align:middle line:84%
But, of course, we all
worry about being on time.

00:46:44.170 --> 00:46:46.280 align:middle line:84%
But-- so she said
one time it was just

00:46:46.280 --> 00:46:49.390 align:middle line:90%
like throwing sand out.

00:46:49.390 --> 00:46:50.700 align:middle line:90%
It scatters everywhere.

00:46:50.700 --> 00:46:52.610 align:middle line:84%
So I believe that
there's a time of-- I

00:46:52.610 --> 00:46:55.430 align:middle line:84%
know the she's taken
care of me, absolutely.

00:46:55.430 --> 00:46:57.590 align:middle line:84%
I know that I've taken
care of her many times.

00:46:57.590 --> 00:47:00.280 align:middle line:84%
And that's also why I
don't judge other families.

00:47:00.280 --> 00:47:02.870 align:middle line:84%
I never look at a family and
say, you need to do what I did.

00:47:02.870 --> 00:47:03.140 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Oh, right.

00:47:03.140 --> 00:47:05.490 align:middle line:84%
>>KAIN: Because I have no idea
what their soul journey is.

00:47:05.490 --> 00:47:06.930 align:middle line:84%
I don't know what
their lesson is.

00:47:06.930 --> 00:47:08.700 align:middle line:90%
And who am I to say anything?

00:47:08.700 --> 00:47:11.390 align:middle line:84%
I just say this is what I
did, and if it calls to you.

00:47:11.390 --> 00:47:13.480 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: Are we all
fulfilling that soul lesson?

00:47:13.480 --> 00:47:15.772 align:middle line:84%
Are we all discovering
it as we go along?

00:47:15.772 --> 00:47:17.980 align:middle line:84%
>>KAIN: I did-- I think
that's what we're here to do.

00:47:17.980 --> 00:47:21.020 align:middle line:84%
And I think that's the
most important thing.

00:47:21.020 --> 00:47:25.620 align:middle line:84%
And I remind myself every day
because most of what I do now

00:47:25.620 --> 00:47:28.980 align:middle line:84%
is communicate with families
and travel and talk to families,

00:47:28.980 --> 00:47:30.830 align:middle line:90%
and it takes a lot.

00:47:30.830 --> 00:47:33.560 align:middle line:84%
And I just remind myself,
life is but a coffee break.

00:47:33.560 --> 00:47:36.290 align:middle line:84%
And when I die, whether
it's tomorrow or today or 10

00:47:36.290 --> 00:47:37.777 align:middle line:84%
years from now or
whatever, I just

00:47:37.777 --> 00:47:39.360 align:middle line:84%
want to look back
and just feel like I

00:47:39.360 --> 00:47:41.620 align:middle line:90%
did what I came here to do.

00:47:41.620 --> 00:47:44.300 align:middle line:84%
And that's my soul purpose,
and in honor of her

00:47:44.300 --> 00:47:45.880 align:middle line:90%
and all of our children.

00:47:45.880 --> 00:47:46.480 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Yes.

00:47:46.480 --> 00:47:48.600 align:middle line:84%
And so what you came
here to do and when

00:47:48.600 --> 00:47:51.240 align:middle line:84%
you go to the conferences and
you speak at the AutismOne

00:47:51.240 --> 00:47:54.195 align:middle line:84%
Conferences and write books
and in your second book

00:47:54.195 --> 00:47:58.920 align:middle line:84%
is more lessons, what is it that
you feel you are here to do?

00:47:58.920 --> 00:48:00.670 align:middle line:84%
>>KAIN: I think I'm
to remind parents

00:48:00.670 --> 00:48:02.370 align:middle line:90%
that everybody's perfect.

00:48:02.370 --> 00:48:05.499 align:middle line:84%
The children are perfect
the way they came in.

00:48:05.499 --> 00:48:07.040 align:middle line:84%
For some reason
there's a lot-- well,

00:48:07.040 --> 00:48:09.970 align:middle line:84%
right now, 50% of our
children have chronic illness.

00:48:09.970 --> 00:48:11.920 align:middle line:84%
I would love to be
part of that change.

00:48:11.920 --> 00:48:14.590 align:middle line:84%
I would like to learn a
lesson in an easier way.

00:48:14.590 --> 00:48:17.930 align:middle line:84%
I felt that I was so
unaware 20 years ago that I

00:48:17.930 --> 00:48:21.360 align:middle line:84%
had to really learn this
lesson in very difficult ways.

00:48:21.360 --> 00:48:23.255 align:middle line:84%
It was very painful
letting go of what

00:48:23.255 --> 00:48:24.630 align:middle line:84%
I thought I was
going to be like.

00:48:24.630 --> 00:48:25.090 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Oh, yes.

00:48:25.090 --> 00:48:25.690 align:middle line:90%
Yeah.

00:48:25.690 --> 00:48:27.490 align:middle line:90%
>>KAIN: And then acceptance.

00:48:27.490 --> 00:48:30.730 align:middle line:84%
So really I think I'm here to
remind parents if I can do it,

00:48:30.730 --> 00:48:31.820 align:middle line:90%
anyone can do it.

00:48:31.820 --> 00:48:35.810 align:middle line:84%
Went through a really difficult
time and I'm still full of joy.

00:48:35.810 --> 00:48:37.740 align:middle line:84%
After she died, it took
a while, of course.

00:48:37.740 --> 00:48:38.240 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Yes,

00:48:38.240 --> 00:48:39.852 align:middle line:90%
>>KAIN: And it's very difficult.

00:48:39.852 --> 00:48:42.060 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: The physical touch
part is, as I can imagine,

00:48:42.060 --> 00:48:44.269 align:middle line:90%
the most challenging--

00:48:44.269 --> 00:48:45.060 align:middle line:90%
>>KAIN: Letting go.

00:48:45.060 --> 00:48:45.601 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Yeah.

00:48:45.601 --> 00:48:48.970 align:middle line:84%
>>KAIN: But my faith tells me
that she's fine where she's at.

00:48:48.970 --> 00:48:51.080 align:middle line:84%
I'm here doing the work
that I agreed to do.

00:48:51.080 --> 00:48:53.540 align:middle line:84%
And I want to do the
best job possible.

00:48:53.540 --> 00:48:56.059 align:middle line:84%
I miss her, but I don't feel
like she's ever far away.

00:48:56.059 --> 00:48:58.100 align:middle line:84%
Of course, I would love
to have her sitting here.

00:48:58.100 --> 00:49:00.183 align:middle line:84%
Then she would just want
me to be quiet, I'm sure,

00:49:00.183 --> 00:49:01.790 align:middle line:90%
and her talk.

00:49:01.790 --> 00:49:04.640 align:middle line:84%
But I'm trying to do my best
to communicate the message

00:49:04.640 --> 00:49:07.832 align:middle line:84%
that she came here to teach, and
it's an honor and a privilege.

00:49:07.832 --> 00:49:10.040 align:middle line:84%
Certainly not the life I
thought I was going to have.

00:49:10.040 --> 00:49:11.900 align:middle line:84%
But it doesn't mean
it's a bad life.

00:49:11.900 --> 00:49:12.020 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: No.

00:49:12.020 --> 00:49:13.061 align:middle line:90%
>>KAIN: It's a good life.

00:49:13.061 --> 00:49:14.300 align:middle line:90%
It's an important life.

00:49:14.300 --> 00:49:18.370 align:middle line:84%
And it's an honor to be able
to be on the other side.

00:49:18.370 --> 00:49:22.020 align:middle line:84%
So I just want to remind parents
that you can get through it.

00:49:22.020 --> 00:49:24.570 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: Now, let's talk a
little bit about the vaccines

00:49:24.570 --> 00:49:27.540 align:middle line:84%
and do you coach
parents who are looking

00:49:27.540 --> 00:49:29.160 align:middle line:90%
at vaccinating their children?

00:49:29.160 --> 00:49:32.730 align:middle line:84%
Are you a voice in
that movement at all?

00:49:32.730 --> 00:49:36.240 align:middle line:84%
>>KAIN: I used to-- I
used to say educate.

00:49:36.240 --> 00:49:38.890 align:middle line:90%
Now I'm a lot more concerned.

00:49:38.890 --> 00:49:41.510 align:middle line:84%
53% of our children
have chronic illness.

00:49:41.510 --> 00:49:45.760 align:middle line:84%
People do not understand
what is in the vaccinations.

00:49:45.760 --> 00:49:49.410 align:middle line:84%
We're giving our kids 49
vaccines by the age of five.

00:49:49.410 --> 00:49:53.970 align:middle line:84%
I talk to parents all over the
US and it's the same story.

00:49:53.970 --> 00:49:55.120 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: 49 vaccines.

00:49:55.120 --> 00:49:57.400 align:middle line:84%
>>KAIN: 49 vaccines by the
time they're age of five.

00:49:57.400 --> 00:49:59.840 align:middle line:84%
That vaccine schedule
has never been tested.

00:49:59.840 --> 00:50:00.990 align:middle line:90%
Our kids are sick.

00:50:00.990 --> 00:50:04.550 align:middle line:90%
We have a huge rate of SIDS.

00:50:04.550 --> 00:50:07.410 align:middle line:84%
And another terrible-- a
couple terrible things.

00:50:07.410 --> 00:50:09.930 align:middle line:84%
I travel all over
and I meet families

00:50:09.930 --> 00:50:12.060 align:middle line:84%
of more than one
vaccine injured child.

00:50:12.060 --> 00:50:13.041 align:middle line:90%
It used to be one.

00:50:13.041 --> 00:50:13.540 align:middle line:90%
Now--

00:50:13.540 --> 00:50:13.930 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Every day.

00:50:13.930 --> 00:50:15.513 align:middle line:84%
>>KAIN: -I was
speaking in Sacramento.

00:50:15.513 --> 00:50:16.830 align:middle line:90%
There were 50 people there.

00:50:16.830 --> 00:50:19.740 align:middle line:84%
There were six families who
had multiple kids with vaccine

00:50:19.740 --> 00:50:21.340 align:middle line:90%
injury.

00:50:21.340 --> 00:50:23.970 align:middle line:84%
We are-- pe-- the
drug companies are

00:50:23.970 --> 00:50:25.940 align:middle line:90%
trying to take our choice away.

00:50:25.940 --> 00:50:28.750 align:middle line:84%
They're vaccinating
six vaccines at a time.

00:50:28.750 --> 00:50:30.895 align:middle line:84%
They're giving eight
vaccines into a little baby

00:50:30.895 --> 00:50:32.850 align:middle line:90%
that you can't feed a banana.

00:50:32.850 --> 00:50:34.030 align:middle line:90%
It's not tested.

00:50:34.030 --> 00:50:35.250 align:middle line:90%
The kids are sick.

00:50:35.250 --> 00:50:42.340 align:middle line:84%
There's a new thing that's
happening where there's

00:50:42.340 --> 00:50:45.380 align:middle line:84%
a warning now to children who
are babysitting to not babysit

00:50:45.380 --> 00:50:50.100 align:middle line:84%
after the kid has been given
a vaccine because parents are

00:50:50.100 --> 00:50:52.590 align:middle line:84%
getting accused of
abusing their children.

00:50:52.590 --> 00:50:54.170 align:middle line:90%
This is becoming very rampant.

00:50:54.170 --> 00:50:56.620 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Explain that again.

00:50:56.620 --> 00:50:59.940 align:middle line:84%
>>KAIN: Well, the vaccine--
kids have vaccinations, right?

00:50:59.940 --> 00:51:01.190 align:middle line:90%
They give them eight vaccines.

00:51:01.190 --> 00:51:02.110 align:middle line:84%
And then all of a
sudden something

00:51:02.110 --> 00:51:03.060 align:middle line:90%
happens to the child--

00:51:03.060 --> 00:51:03.570 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Oh.

00:51:03.570 --> 00:51:04.920 align:middle line:84%
>>KAIN: -and then the
child gets brain damaged.

00:51:04.920 --> 00:51:06.490 align:middle line:84%
And then the parents
are being blamed

00:51:06.490 --> 00:51:08.000 align:middle line:90%
for shaken baby or something.

00:51:08.000 --> 00:51:10.370 align:middle line:84%
And this is becoming
a new epidemic

00:51:10.370 --> 00:51:13.170 align:middle line:84%
of parents being accused
of abusing their children.

00:51:13.170 --> 00:51:15.640 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: As you had
experienced a little bit of.

00:51:15.640 --> 00:51:17.289 align:middle line:84%
They actually tried
to blame it on you?

00:51:17.289 --> 00:51:17.830 align:middle line:90%
The seizures?

00:51:17.830 --> 00:51:18.570 align:middle line:90%
>>KAIN: No, they didn't.

00:51:18.570 --> 00:51:19.069 align:middle line:90%
No.

00:51:19.069 --> 00:51:21.334 align:middle line:84%
Because I was in
a doctor's office

00:51:21.334 --> 00:51:22.500 align:middle line:90%
two hours after the vaccine.

00:51:22.500 --> 00:51:22.980 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Right.

00:51:22.980 --> 00:51:24.520 align:middle line:84%
>>KAIN: But this
is sometimes where

00:51:24.520 --> 00:51:27.297 align:middle line:84%
it happens days later or hours
later where all of a sudden

00:51:27.297 --> 00:51:29.130 align:middle line:84%
there was a healthy
baby, and then they come

00:51:29.130 --> 00:51:30.963 align:middle line:84%
and the baby is really
sick or brain injured

00:51:30.963 --> 00:51:33.477 align:middle line:84%
and the government is
blaming the parents.

00:51:33.477 --> 00:51:34.310 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: The parents.

00:51:34.310 --> 00:51:35.940 align:middle line:84%
>>KAIN: Or the
babysitter or anybody.

00:51:35.940 --> 00:51:41.149 align:middle line:84%
And so parents are getting
arrested for abusing their kid.

00:51:41.149 --> 00:51:41.940 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Oh, my god.

00:51:41.940 --> 00:51:42.770 align:middle line:90%
>>KAIN: Yeah, it's crazy.

00:51:42.770 --> 00:51:43.269 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Wow.

00:51:43.269 --> 00:51:45.989 align:middle line:90%
So what do you do instead?

00:51:45.989 --> 00:51:47.780 align:middle line:84%
>>KAIN: Well, I think
we need to figure out

00:51:47.780 --> 00:51:49.240 align:middle line:84%
why we're giving
so many vaccines

00:51:49.240 --> 00:51:51.960 align:middle line:84%
and why are we doing a hepatitis
B vaccine the first day of life

00:51:51.960 --> 00:51:53.540 align:middle line:90%
and is that necessary?

00:51:53.540 --> 00:51:55.300 align:middle line:90%
I don't believe it is.

00:51:55.300 --> 00:51:57.710 align:middle line:84%
I wouldn't give six
vaccines to anybody.

00:51:57.710 --> 00:52:00.090 align:middle line:84%
And to really look at
it, it's just a fear.

00:52:00.090 --> 00:52:02.147 align:middle line:84%
And the doctors are
bullying parents.

00:52:02.147 --> 00:52:03.980 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: It was different
when we were young.

00:52:03.980 --> 00:52:06.527 align:middle line:84%
There was only about five
or six when we were young--

00:52:06.527 --> 00:52:07.860 align:middle line:90%
>>KAIN: Maybe five or six, yeah.

00:52:07.860 --> 00:52:10.200 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: -adults-- that
adults went through.

00:52:10.200 --> 00:52:13.610 align:middle line:90%
And now there's almost 50.

00:52:13.610 --> 00:52:14.300 align:middle line:90%
>>KAIN: Right.

00:52:14.300 --> 00:52:17.720 align:middle line:84%
There's 49 vaccines now and,
of course, they want more.

00:52:17.720 --> 00:52:20.380 align:middle line:84%
And they're not liable for
what happens to the kids

00:52:20.380 --> 00:52:22.840 align:middle line:84%
and the doctors
are kicking parents

00:52:22.840 --> 00:52:24.540 align:middle line:90%
out for not vaccinating them.

00:52:24.540 --> 00:52:27.390 align:middle line:84%
But I have to tell you,
I see healthy babies--

00:52:27.390 --> 00:52:30.820 align:middle line:84%
the healthiest babies I see are
breastfed and not vaccinated,

00:52:30.820 --> 00:52:31.902 align:middle line:90%
and they're thriving.

00:52:31.902 --> 00:52:34.110 align:middle line:84%
And the kids that are
vaccinated have the same story.

00:52:34.110 --> 00:52:35.720 align:middle line:84%
They were vaccinated,
then they get sick,

00:52:35.720 --> 00:52:37.750 align:middle line:84%
and then they're on
antibiotics, and more vaccines,

00:52:37.750 --> 00:52:38.510 align:middle line:90%
more antibiotics.

00:52:38.510 --> 00:52:41.710 align:middle line:84%
The doctor keeps telling the
parents that this is fine,

00:52:41.710 --> 00:52:44.130 align:middle line:84%
and then all of a sudden,
they're really sick.

00:52:44.130 --> 00:52:46.070 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: And it's also
the emotional disorders.

00:52:46.070 --> 00:52:47.694 align:middle line:84%
And I'm not saying
that this is linked,

00:52:47.694 --> 00:52:50.520 align:middle line:84%
but it doesn't necessarily
have to be infections.

00:52:50.520 --> 00:52:55.570 align:middle line:84%
It could be anxiety, depression,
schizophrenia, anything

00:52:55.570 --> 00:52:59.330 align:middle line:84%
that has to do with emotional
or mental disorders as well.

00:52:59.330 --> 00:53:01.810 align:middle line:84%
I have read that
there are links,

00:53:01.810 --> 00:53:04.910 align:middle line:84%
but there isn't-- there's no
way to be able to prove anything

00:53:04.910 --> 00:53:06.310 align:middle line:90%
like that at this point.

00:53:06.310 --> 00:53:08.080 align:middle line:84%
>>KAIN: We have-- we
have a sick society,

00:53:08.080 --> 00:53:09.204 align:middle line:90%
and this is a huge concern.

00:53:09.204 --> 00:53:11.440 align:middle line:84%
We have 1 in 68
children with autism,

00:53:11.440 --> 00:53:14.720 align:middle line:90%
and that's a very low figure.

00:53:14.720 --> 00:53:16.410 align:middle line:90%
There's a lot more than that.

00:53:16.410 --> 00:53:18.720 align:middle line:84%
Our kids have diabetes,
they have chronic illness,

00:53:18.720 --> 00:53:19.960 align:middle line:90%
they have seizures, asthma.

00:53:19.960 --> 00:53:22.510 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: Well, even if there's
no way to directly link

00:53:22.510 --> 00:53:27.141 align:middle line:84%
and if there is-- because
it's-- there's no emphasis

00:53:27.141 --> 00:53:29.640 align:middle line:84%
on the direct link, there's not
enough research that's being

00:53:29.640 --> 00:53:31.820 align:middle line:84%
done about it, those
studies won't be funded.

00:53:31.820 --> 00:53:35.420 align:middle line:84%
So the only thing that we
can do is to raise awareness

00:53:35.420 --> 00:53:37.020 align:middle line:90%
and to do your own research.

00:53:37.020 --> 00:53:40.029 align:middle line:84%
And you have brought
that for the one person

00:53:40.029 --> 00:53:42.070 align:middle line:84%
that has never heard of
this before in their life

00:53:42.070 --> 00:53:44.700 align:middle line:84%
and they're seeing this show
right now for the first time,

00:53:44.700 --> 00:53:47.170 align:middle line:84%
they're going to go tell
someone else watch this.

00:53:47.170 --> 00:53:49.190 align:middle line:84%
Listen to this lady
before you consider

00:53:49.190 --> 00:53:50.390 align:middle line:90%
vaccinating your child.

00:53:50.390 --> 00:53:52.990 align:middle line:84%
Do your research,
ask your doctor,

00:53:52.990 --> 00:53:55.300 align:middle line:84%
find a doctor who
doesn't vaccinate and see

00:53:55.300 --> 00:53:57.060 align:middle line:90%
what their opinions are.

00:53:57.060 --> 00:53:59.070 align:middle line:84%
There's so much--
there's such a long road

00:53:59.070 --> 00:54:01.450 align:middle line:84%
that you have to go on,
which is a very good road.

00:54:01.450 --> 00:54:02.989 align:middle line:90%
It's a much needed road.

00:54:02.989 --> 00:54:03.780 align:middle line:90%
>>KAIN: Absolutely.

00:54:03.780 --> 00:54:04.480 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Much needed.

00:54:04.480 --> 00:54:06.650 align:middle line:84%
>>KAIN: We're putting toxins
into our kids and our kids are

00:54:06.650 --> 00:54:08.858 align:middle line:84%
sick, and then everyone is
was walking around blaming

00:54:08.858 --> 00:54:11.480 align:middle line:84%
the parent or-- you know,
it's always back to blaming

00:54:11.480 --> 00:54:12.299 align:middle line:90%
the parent and--

00:54:12.299 --> 00:54:12.840 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Yeah.

00:54:12.840 --> 00:54:15.880 align:middle line:84%
>>KAIN: -we need to start really
raising awareness and talking

00:54:15.880 --> 00:54:18.940 align:middle line:84%
about it and demanding
research to be done.

00:54:18.940 --> 00:54:20.610 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: Well, I want
to end on the note

00:54:20.610 --> 00:54:23.710 align:middle line:84%
of a few of the spiritual
tips that you do tell us

00:54:23.710 --> 00:54:25.700 align:middle line:84%
and that you have
gathered from all this.

00:54:25.700 --> 00:54:29.200 align:middle line:84%
And I know that you have so much
more to say, but one of them

00:54:29.200 --> 00:54:32.820 align:middle line:84%
is each soul has something
to contribute, yes?

00:54:32.820 --> 00:54:34.590 align:middle line:90%
Make it fun.

00:54:34.590 --> 00:54:36.390 align:middle line:84%
What you do on an
individual level

00:54:36.390 --> 00:54:38.520 align:middle line:84%
affects your surrounding,
your children.

00:54:38.520 --> 00:54:41.480 align:middle line:84%
We didn't talk about that as
much, but what do you mean?

00:54:41.480 --> 00:54:43.724 align:middle line:84%
What you do with
yourself affects--

00:54:43.724 --> 00:54:44.890 align:middle line:90%
>>KAIN: I think everything--

00:54:44.890 --> 00:54:46.390 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: You're
mirroring constantly.

00:54:46.390 --> 00:54:49.780 align:middle line:84%
>>KAIN: How we feel and
who we are, And it's

00:54:49.780 --> 00:54:52.270 align:middle line:84%
like all the little things
kind of make up the big things.

00:54:52.270 --> 00:54:55.330 align:middle line:84%
So if I'm walking around
really angry and unloving,

00:54:55.330 --> 00:54:57.540 align:middle line:84%
I'm sure my child or
anybody doesn't really

00:54:57.540 --> 00:54:58.810 align:middle line:90%
want to be around me.

00:54:58.810 --> 00:54:59.460 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Right.

00:54:59.460 --> 00:55:00.246 align:middle line:90%
Right.

00:55:00.246 --> 00:55:01.620 align:middle line:84%
We talked about
the world that we

00:55:01.620 --> 00:55:04.780 align:middle line:84%
live in is a projection
of our own thoughts.

00:55:04.780 --> 00:55:09.090 align:middle line:84%
And finally, that we're part
of a greater whole connected

00:55:09.090 --> 00:55:14.160 align:middle line:84%
in a fundamental way, and
what I do to you affects me.

00:55:14.160 --> 00:55:17.260 align:middle line:84%
And that is a beautiful
way to live your life,

00:55:17.260 --> 00:55:18.910 align:middle line:90%
even if you have a child or not.

00:55:18.910 --> 00:55:21.660 align:middle line:84%
What I do affects
you and affects me.

00:55:21.660 --> 00:55:24.210 align:middle line:84%
So that's a beautiful
way to wrap up.

00:55:24.210 --> 00:55:25.150 align:middle line:90%
Thank you so much.

00:55:25.150 --> 00:55:26.040 align:middle line:90%
You're amazing.

00:55:26.040 --> 00:55:27.761 align:middle line:90%
I could talk to you forever.

00:55:27.761 --> 00:55:28.510 align:middle line:90%
>>KAIN: Thank you.

00:55:28.510 --> 00:55:30.218 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: Thank you for
being so courageous

00:55:30.218 --> 00:55:31.930 align:middle line:90%
and being such an inspiration.

00:55:31.930 --> 00:55:32.680 align:middle line:90%
You're incredible.

00:55:32.680 --> 00:55:32.940 align:middle line:90%
>>KAIN: Thank you.

00:55:32.940 --> 00:55:33.439 align:middle line:90%
Thank you.

